": 2048}, {\"ngram\": \"Year\", \"from\": 2055, \"to\": 2059}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I think Brady will be better than conventional wisdom might suggest, especially as the season goes along.\", \"from\": 2064, \"to\": 2169, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Brady\", \"from\": 2072, \"to\": 2077}, {\"ngram\": \"conventional wisdom\", \"from\": 2098, \"to\": 2117}, {\"ngram\": \"the season\", \"from\": 2147, \"to\": 2157}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He was never Charles Barkley in open press conferences - measured and calculated - but this is the case for most famous NFL quarterbacks.\", \"from\": 2170, \"to\": 2307, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2183, \"end\": 2198, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_Barkley\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2105833170371255e-23, \"text\": \"Charles Barkley\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_Barkley\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_Barkley\"}, {\"begin\": 2290, \"end\": 2293, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NFL_on_Fox\", \"score\": 0.9998903843526235, \"rank\": 0.00010962766459667974, \"text\": \"NFL\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q15416\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NFL_on_Fox\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NFL_on_Fox\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"open press conferences\", \"from\": 2202, \"to\": 2224}, {\"ngram\": \"the case\", \"from\": 2265, \"to\": 2273}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There are a lot of different ways to be an effective game analyst: Tony Romo is different than Peyton Manning, who is different than Troy Aikman, who is different than Charles Davis.Brady's lead producer and director have 60 years of experiencebetween them and sideline reporters with a ton of broadcast miles.\", \"from\": 2308, \"to\": 2618, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2375, \"end\": 2384, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Romo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tony Romo\